{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"849f1b05-f0a7-4895-8502-ffcc0bad0c22","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet --version` to confirm the SDK, then `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` to catch any breaking changes. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for any API or behavioral changes that may affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1fa70b4a-bf6c-47bc-b1c1-0cc3c1044b0d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question — I don't need to search their codebase since they've described the files. Let me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":296},"id":"a80cb40c-05d1-4f57-91aa-31b693450b34","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:59:07.960Z","parentId":"b638d883-79dd-4a50-a4cd-94dbbc85fa4f"}
